# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: BlackMonolith | Scene: TheBlackMonolithMage11
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah had woken early the next day."
    new "Sarah had woken early the next day."

    old "She had quietly sneaked out of bed, leaving Samayra to get a few extra hours of sleep."
    new "She had quietly sneaked out of bed, leaving Samayra to get a few extra hours of sleep."

    old "The girl needed it, she had seemed exhausted these last few weeks."
    new "The girl needed it, she had seemed exhausted these last few weeks."

    old "She sat behind her desk, looking out over the pile of work that she had somehow managed to attract."
    new "She sat behind her desk, looking out over the pile of work that she had somehow managed to attract."

    old "Books from Metis. Books from Razaphel. Books for her own study. Practicing magic."
    new "Books from Metis. Books from Razaphel. Books for her own study. Practicing magic."

    old "When she added it all up in her head, it seemed like a mountain."
    new "When she added it all up in her head, it seemed like a mountain."

    old "And yet, climbing a mountain required a first step, and so Sarah found herself pressing herself to the work."
    new "And yet, climbing a mountain required a first step, and so Sarah found herself pressing herself to the work."

    old "Like a blade to a whetstone, she could feel herself sharpening."
    new "Like a blade to a whetstone, she could feel herself sharpening."

    old "She hadn't long begun when she suddenly heard a noise."
    new "She hadn't long begun when she suddenly heard a noise."

    old "Metis entered the room."
    new "Metis entered the room."

    old "Sarah could see something was different about him. It took her a moment to realize the packed bags near his feet."
    new "Sarah could see something was different about him. It took her a moment to realize the packed bags near his feet."

    old "You're leaving?"
    new "You're leaving?"

    old "Sarah was surprised at the fact that she found herself shocked."
    new "Sarah was surprised at the fact that she found herself shocked."

    old "It wasn't that long ago that she would have gladly pushed him out onto the street."
    new "It wasn't that long ago that she would have gladly pushed him out onto the street."

    old "Yeah, the ship I chartered came in a few weeks early."
    new "Yeah, the ship I chartered came in a few weeks early."

    old "I know I promised to train you for longer, but the truth is I have my own work to see to."
    new "I know I promised to train you for longer, but the truth is I have my own work to see to."

    old "Now with the ship coming in early, it means I can get where I need to go faster."
    new "Now with the ship coming in early, it means I can get where I need to go faster."

    old "Sarah looked at him from across the desk."
    new "Sarah looked at him from across the desk."

    old "And where is that?"
    new "And where is that?"

    old "Keep asking questions, I like that about you."
    new "Keep asking questions, I like that about you."

    old "A reply, but not an answer."
    new "A reply, but not an answer."

    old "Tell you what, if I get back we can pick up on the lessons. In between, keep studying and practice. But don't go pushing yourself."
    new "Tell you what, if I get back we can pick up on the lessons. In between, keep studying and practice. But don't go pushing yourself."

    old "Sarah noticed he was quickly changing the subject from where he was going, back to her lessons."
    new "Sarah noticed he was quickly changing the subject from where he was going, back to her lessons."

    old "She could press him, but she also knew there was a reason he wasn't answering."
    new "She could press him, but she also knew there was a reason he wasn't answering."

    old "Also, she doubted he'd be tripped up by her asking him more questions."
    new "Also, she doubted he'd be tripped up by her asking him more questions."

    old "Well, I think I'll be sad to see you leave."
    new "Well, I think I'll be sad to see you leave."

    old "And I don't think I'll be the only one. Samayra was happy for the company."
    new "And I don't think I'll be the only one. Samayra was happy for the company."

    old "She's a good kid. I think she's lucky to have you for a friend."
    new "She's a good kid. I think she's lucky to have you for a friend."

    old "He looked around to see if there was anyone else around."
    new "He looked around to see if there was anyone else around."

    old "I heard she had a surprise for you."
    new "I heard she had a surprise for you."

    old "Please, don't pull it out of me. I vowed to keep quiet about it. She made me swear on the Gods and everything."
    new "Please, don't pull it out of me. I vowed to keep quiet about it. She made me swear on the Gods and everything."

    old "Sarah frowned. She wasn't much for surprises."
    new "Sarah frowned. She wasn't much for surprises."

    old "Tell her I said goodbye, I regret not being able to do it properly."
    new "Tell her I said goodbye, I regret not being able to do it properly."

    old "I'll tell her."
    new "I'll tell her."

    old "Metis sighed and picked up his bags."
    new "Metis sighed and picked up his bags."

    old "Well, I'm sad to see our encounter cut so short, but I'm sure we will meet again."
    new "Well, I'm sad to see our encounter cut so short, but I'm sure we will meet again."

    old "Sarah looked at him intently. Had he ever discovered or suspected anything related to Xan?"
    new "Sarah looked at him intently. Had he ever discovered or suspected anything related to Xan?"

    old "If he had, he still gave no hint of it."
    new "If he had, he still gave no hint of it."

    old "Tell me, if you ever see that weird little spirit, can you tell him I said hello?"
    new "Tell me, if you ever see that weird little spirit, can you tell him I said hello?"

    old "Razaphel never came to see you?"
    new "Razaphel never came to see you?"

    old "Who is to speculate on the mind of such a creature. I only worry myself about the questions that can actually be answered."
    new "Who is to speculate on the mind of such a creature. I only worry myself about the questions that can actually be answered."

    old "Metis chuckled again, amused with himself."
    new "Metis chuckled again, amused with himself."

    old "He made a motion for the door before suddenly stopping."
    new "He made a motion for the door before suddenly stopping."

    old "Aah, I almost forgot!"
    new "Aah, I almost forgot!"

    old "Honestly, it's like my husband always says, if my head wasn't attached to me I'd lose it."
    new "Honestly, it's like my husband always says, if my head wasn't attached to me I'd lose it."

    old "Sarah frowned. Husband?"
    new "Sarah frowned. Husband?"

    old "Metis closed the distance between them, standing on the opposite side of the desk."
    new "Metis closed the distance between them, standing on the opposite side of the desk."

    old "He reached into his pocket and produced a letter."
    new "He reached into his pocket and produced a letter."

    old "Casually, he threw it onto the desk."
    new "Casually, he threw it onto the desk."

    old "When Xan comes back, can you give him that?"
    new "When Xan comes back, can you give him that?"

    old "I had hoped to speak with him directly, but now with the ship and all that...it's too much trouble and I'd rather it didn't wait."
    new "I had hoped to speak with him directly, but now with the ship and all that...it's too much trouble and I'd rather it didn't wait."

    old "Just hand him that and I guess that will have to do. I've written it all down in there."
    new "Just hand him that and I guess that will have to do. I've written it all down in there."

    old "Sarah held the letter in her hand. A wax seal sat atop it, keeping it closed."
    new "Sarah held the letter in her hand. A wax seal sat atop it, keeping it closed."

    old "Is this going to explode if it accidentally opens up?"
    new "Is this going to explode if it accidentally opens up?"

    old "Metis raised one eyebrow."
    new "Metis raised one eyebrow."

    old "It's just a letter Sarah. Not everything is magic."
    new "It's just a letter Sarah. Not everything is magic."

    old "He turned and walked towards the door, turning just before leaving."
    new "He turned and walked towards the door, turning just before leaving."

    old "Stay safe, Sarah. Dangerous times out there."
    new "Stay safe, Sarah. Dangerous times out there."

    old "Sarah looked at him, unsure of what to make of his remark."
    new "Sarah looked at him, unsure of what to make of his remark."

    old "You stay safe as well. And you're always welcome here."
    new "You stay safe as well. And you're always welcome here."

    old "Metis smiled, but said nothing."
    new "Metis smiled, but said nothing."

    old "He gave her one last short wave and then stepped out through the door."
    new "He gave her one last short wave and then stepped out through the door."

    old "Sarah watched through the window has he made his way to the harbor."
    new "Sarah watched through the window has he made his way to the harbor."

    old "Towards his ship that would take him...wherever it was."
    new "Towards his ship that would take him...wherever it was."

    old "Sarah considered the man for a moment longer."
    new "Sarah considered the man for a moment longer."

    old "Appearing out of nowhere. Acting too familiar."
    new "Appearing out of nowhere. Acting too familiar."

    old "On the other hand, he seemed friendly enough and even decided to teach her."
    new "On the other hand, he seemed friendly enough and even decided to teach her."

    old "Was he send here to spy? Just an accidental visit?"
    new "Was he send here to spy? Just an accidental visit?"

    old "Sarah sighed. She was no closer to an answer than when she had first met him."
    new "Sarah sighed. She was no closer to an answer than when she had first met him."

    old "Whatever else it was, he was gone now."
    new "Whatever else it was, he was gone now."

    old "That gave her time. Space. To think."
    new "That gave her time. Space. To think."

    old "Sitting in the chair, Sarah felt her eyes slowly glide towards the desk."
    new "Sitting in the chair, Sarah felt her eyes slowly glide towards the desk."

    old "Towards the letter on top of everything else."
    new "Towards the letter on top of everything else."

    old "A green wax seal covered the front."
    new "A green wax seal covered the front."

    old "She held it in her hand, passing it from one to the other, as if hoping to divine the content by weight."
    new "She held it in her hand, passing it from one to the other, as if hoping to divine the content by weight."

    old "A letter of Xan, from Metis. Explaining what he had come here to tell him in the first place..."
    new "A letter of Xan, from Metis. Explaining what he had come here to tell him in the first place..."

    old "She had to open it. To know...to understand..."
    new "She had to open it. To know...to understand..."

    old "Still, a part of her was hesitant. It was an ordinary letter, she felt no magical energy coming from it."
    new "Still, a part of her was hesitant. It was an ordinary letter, she felt no magical energy coming from it."

    old "And still some part of her was always like that...hestitant."
    new "And still some part of her was always like that...hestitant."

    old "She threw the letter back on top of the desk."
    new "She threw the letter back on top of the desk."

    old "Whatever it was, it could wait. At least until she was sure Metis was on his ship and heading out the city."
    new "Whatever it was, it could wait. At least until she was sure Metis was on his ship and heading out the city."

    old "She had only just thrown the letter back when she heard a noise."
    new "She had only just thrown the letter back when she heard a noise."

    old "Soft, like a mouse."
    new "Soft, like a mouse."

    old "I can hear you."
    new "I can hear you."

    old "Samayra stuck her head around the corner, smiling."
    new "Samayra stuck her head around the corner, smiling."

    old "You caught me."
    new "You caught me."

    old "Samayra stepped into the room properly and frowned."
    new "Samayra stepped into the room properly and frowned."

    old "How do you manage to hear me anway? Servants used to be scared of me because they didn't hear me walk up on them."
    new "How do you manage to hear me anway? Servants used to be scared of me because they didn't hear me walk up on them."

    old "The sneaking monster of Bagrad, Samayra-the-terrible."
    new "The sneaking monster of Bagrad, Samayra-the-terrible."

    old "But honestly, I just had a lot of practice. Thomas used to be like you. Always walking so softly."
    new "But honestly, I just had a lot of practice. Thomas used to be like you. Always walking so softly."

    old "You spend years keeping your ears out for it, I guess you develop a talent."
    new "You spend years keeping your ears out for it, I guess you develop a talent."

    old "Samayra walked further into the room, leaning across the desk."
    new "Samayra walked further into the room, leaning across the desk."

    old "Have you seen Metis?"
    new "Have you seen Metis?"

    old "He just left actually. Only a few minutes ago."
    new "He just left actually. Only a few minutes ago."

    old "Samayra frowned."
    new "Samayra frowned."

    old "Really? He didn't even say goodbye...he was supposed to help me."
    new "Really? He didn't even say goodbye...he was supposed to help me."

    old "He asked me to tell you that he said goodbye."
    new "He asked me to tell you that he said goodbye."

    old "And help you with what...exactly?"
    new "And help you with what...exactly?"

    old "Samayra's face turned into a wide grin."
    new "Samayra's face turned into a wide grin."

    old "I got a surprise for you!"
    new "I got a surprise for you!"

    old "Have I ever told you I hate surprises?"
    new "Have I ever told you I hate surprises?"

    old "Ugh, don't be so dour. I practiced really hard on this!"
    new "Ugh, don't be so dour. I practiced really hard on this!"

    old "Sarah looked at the girl, confused."
    new "Sarah looked at the girl, confused."

    old "Practiced what?"
    new "Practiced what?"

    old "Just look!"
    new "Just look!"

    old "Samayra jumped back into the center of the room."
    new "Samayra jumped back into the center of the room."

    old "She held out her hand."
    new "She held out her hand."

    old "Sarah leaned forward, looking intently."
    new "Sarah leaned forward, looking intently."

    old "She felt it before she saw it."
    new "She felt it before she saw it."

    old "A shift in the magical energy."
    new "A shift in the magical energy."

    old "The energy in the room condensed into the palm of Samayra's hand."
    new "The energy in the room condensed into the palm of Samayra's hand."

    old "Forming out of nothingness, a small pale blue flame emerged."
    new "Forming out of nothingness, a small pale blue flame emerged."

    old "Slowly, the flame grew, wrapping itself harmlessly around the girl's hands."
    new "Slowly, the flame grew, wrapping itself harmlessly around the girl's hands."

    old "The magical fire cast a blue-ish hue over the room."
    new "The magical fire cast a blue-ish hue over the room."

    old "And above all."
    new "And above all."

    old "The girl was crowned in starlight."
    new "The girl was crowned in starlight."

    old "Sarah was stunned at the sight."
    new "Sarah was stunned at the sight."

    old "Samayra was doing magic, however simplistic...she was doing it."
    new "Samayra was doing magic, however simplistic...she was doing it."

    old "How...how are you...doing this..."
    new "How...how are you...doing this..."

    old "She saw past the fire, Samayra's wide smile."
    new "She saw past the fire, Samayra's wide smile."

    old "Awesome, isn't it?!"
    new "Awesome, isn't it?!"

    old "I mean, you thought that I might be able to do it, so...I mean I asked Metis!"
    new "I mean, you thought that I might be able to do it, so...I mean I asked Metis!"

    old "You were so busy that you didn't always have time for me, so I thought Metis could help me out."
    new "You were so busy that you didn't always have time for me, so I thought Metis could help me out."

    old "And he did!"
    new "And he did!"

    old "He showed me all the basics, and at first I thought I was terrible at it, I could not do it at all!"
    new "He showed me all the basics, and at first I thought I was terrible at it, I could not do it at all!"

    old "I was just waving my hands like I was silly, but then it just clicked!"
    new "I was just waving my hands like I was silly, but then it just clicked!"

    old "And now..."
    new "And now..."

    old "Samayra moved her hand, the flame following along."
    new "Samayra moved her hand, the flame following along."

    old "See! I can actually do it!"
    new "See! I can actually do it!"

    old "I'm a mage, like you!"
    new "I'm a mage, like you!"

    old "Sarah saw the girl's face twist into embarrassment."
    new "Sarah saw the girl's face twist into embarrassment."

    old "I mean...well...not like you, of course, you're way better, but you know..."
    new "I mean...well...not like you, of course, you're way better, but you know..."

    old "Sarah jumped up from her chair."
    new "Sarah jumped up from her chair."

    old "Samayra! This is amazing!"
    new "Samayra! This is amazing!"

    old "She saw Samayra's face turn back into that beaming smile."
    new "She saw Samayra's face turn back into that beaming smile."

    old "Really? You really think so?"
    new "Really? You really think so?"

    old "Sarah nodded. She meant every word of it."
    new "Sarah nodded. She meant every word of it."

    old "Yeah...you learned this so fast!"
    new "Yeah...you learned this so fast!"

    old "Samayra was turning red from the praise."
    new "Samayra was turning red from the praise."

    old "I mean...without Metis I wouldn't have managed...but..."
    new "I mean...without Metis I wouldn't have managed...but..."

    old "Sarah snuffed out the flame from Samayra's palm, a trivial effort for her."
    new "Sarah snuffed out the flame from Samayra's palm, a trivial effort for her."

    old "Then she rushed forward and caught the girl in an embrace."
    new "Then she rushed forward and caught the girl in an embrace."

    old "Sarah was far from the strongest, but even to her, lifting Samayra off the ground and spinning her proved hardly difficult."
    new "Sarah was far from the strongest, but even to her, lifting Samayra off the ground and spinning her proved hardly difficult."

    old "Samayra shrieked as Sarah spun her around, before finally putting her back down."
    new "Samayra shrieked as Sarah spun her around, before finally putting her back down."

    old "Wow...we're going to do amazing things together. I just know it."
    new "Wow...we're going to do amazing things together. I just know it."

    old "Samayra smiled at her. Her piercing eyes cutting into Sarah's."
    new "Samayra smiled at her. Her piercing eyes cutting into Sarah's."

    old "If Metis left...I guess I don't have a teacher anymore."
    new "If Metis left...I guess I don't have a teacher anymore."

    old "The girl slightly paused before asking the question Sarah was expecting."
    new "The girl slightly paused before asking the question Sarah was expecting."

    old "Would you want to be my teacher?"
    new "Would you want to be my teacher?"

    old "Of course, you don't even have to ask."
    new "Of course, you don't even have to ask."

    old "For the rest of the day, Sarah spend it with Samayra."
    new "For the rest of the day, Sarah spend it with Samayra."

    old "The girl told her how she had followed her lessons in secret."
    new "The girl told her how she had followed her lessons in secret."

    old "How Metis had taken her through all the basics steps, how she had struggled, and how she had finally managed it."
    new "How Metis had taken her through all the basics steps, how she had struggled, and how she had finally managed it."

    old "Her magic wasn't much, but it was a spark, and that was all that was needed to grow."
    new "Her magic wasn't much, but it was a spark, and that was all that was needed to grow."

    old "So lost in this surprise, Sarah all but forgot about the letter for most of that day."
    new "So lost in this surprise, Sarah all but forgot about the letter for most of that day."

    old "Instead, she looked on in awe at what Samayra was. What she was becoming."
    new "Instead, she looked on in awe at what Samayra was. What she was becoming."

    old "Sarah decided to distract herself with the one thing that always worked. Work."
    new "Sarah decided to distract herself with the one thing that always worked. Work."

